---
description: GitHub and Linear workflow rules
alwaysApply: true
---

Use this workflow:

1. Every task should be linked to a Linear issue when available.
2. Branch naming format:
   - feature/LIN-123-short-description
   - fix/LIN-123-short-description
   - chore/LIN-123-short-description
   - docs/LIN-123-short-description
3. Commit messages must follow Conventional Commits:
   - feat: add attendance join flow
   - fix: correct Prisma client initialization
   - chore: update CI workflow
   - docs: update deployment guide
4. Pull request title should follow the same convention.
5. Pull request body must include:
   - Summary
   - Changes
   - Tests performed
   - Linked issue: Closes LIN-123
6. Do not merge to main directly.
7. Prefer pull requests over direct commits to main.
